cards.name: Oddish

attacks.name: Leaf Boomerang
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

cards.flavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

cards.name: Gloom

attacks.name: Offensive Scent
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

cards.flavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

cards.name: Bellossom

attacks.name: Flower Spin
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads. Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

cards.name: Tangela
cards.flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon's true appearance remains a mystery.

cards.name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Suctioning Vines
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

cards.name: Scyther

attacks.name: Mach Cut
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: As Scyther fights more and more battles, its scythes become sharper and sharper. With a single slice, Scyther can fell a massive tree.

cards.name: Sunkern
cards.flavorText: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

cards.name: Yanma

attacks.name: Swoop Across
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

cards.name: Yanmega

attacks.name: Shoot Through
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Jet Wing
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

cards.flavorText: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

cards.name: Kricketot

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

cards.flavorText: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

cards.name: Cherubi
cards.flavorText: The deeper a Cherubi's red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

cards.name: Carnivine

attacks.name: Festering Saliva
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

cards.flavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

cards.name: Leafeon V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Leaf Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Slashing Strike
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike.

rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Leaf Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

cards.name: Grubbin

attacks.name: Energize
attacks.text: Attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.flavorText: It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.

cards.name: Zarude

attacks.name: Drag Off
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to the new Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Triple Whip
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

cards.flavorText: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

cards.name: Calyrex

attacks.name: King's Instructions
attacks.text: You may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Bloomshine
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

cards.name: Charizard V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Incinerate
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.name: Charizard VSTAR
rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

attacks.name: Explosive Fire
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

cards.name: Radiant Charizard

abilities.name: Excited Heart
abilities.text: This Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless less for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

rules: Radiant Pokémon rule: You can't have more than 1 Radiant Pokémon in your deck.

attacks.name: Combustion Blast
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Combustion Blast.

cards.flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

cards.name: Entei

abilities.name: Explosive Heat Dash
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Fire Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

cards.flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

cards.name: Simisear V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Bursting Power
attacks.text: You may attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your hand to your Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Flare Juggling
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.name: Simisear VSTAR
rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

VSTAR Power
Fire → Ember Star : 30×
This attack does 30 damage for each Energy card in your discard pile. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

attacks.name: Fireball Fever
attacks.text: You may discard up to 5 cards from the top of your deck. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

cards.name: Larvesta
cards.flavorText: The people of ancient times believed that Larvesta fell from the sun.

cards.name: Volcarona

attacks.name: Volcanic Heat
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

cards.flavorText: Volcarona scatters burning scales. Some say it does this to start fires. Others say it's trying to rescue those that suffer in the cold.

cards.name: Volcanion

attacks.name: Hydro Burn
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Water Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

cards.flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

cards.name: Salandit

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.flavorText: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokémon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit's poisonous gas.

cards.name: Salazzle

attacks.name: Tail Trickery
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Super Singe
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

cards.flavorText: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.

cards.name: Seel
cards.flavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don't bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

cards.name: Galarian Mr. Mime

attacks.name: Find It
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.flavorText: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of itsnfeet. It'll spend the whole day tap-dancing on anfrozen floor.

cards.name: Wailmer

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

cards.name: Wailord

attacks.name: Bubble Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

cards.name: Corphish
cards.flavorText: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

cards.name: Snorunt
cards.flavorText: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.

cards.name: Luvdisc

attacks.name: Emotional Draw
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 5 cards.

cards.flavorText: Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola's branches.

cards.name: Kyogre

attacks.name: Wave Summoning
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Water Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Dynamic Wave
attacks.text: Put 3 Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand. This attack does 180 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

cards.name: Kyogre V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dual Splash
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Aqua Typhoon
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Aqua Typhoon.

cards.name: Glaceon V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Frost Charge
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Water Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.name: Shinx
cards.flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

cards.name: Shinx

attacks.name: Thunder Jolt
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.

cards.name: Luxio

attacks.name: Jumping Kick
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

cards.name: Luxio

attacks.name: Shorting Spark
attacks.text: This attack does 90 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon that has a Pokémon Tool attached. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: By joining its tail with that of another Luxio, this Pokémon can receive some of the other Luxio's electricity and power up its own electric blasts.

cards.name: Luxray

attacks.name: Electrostep
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Scar Strikes
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

cards.flavorText: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

cards.name: Luxray

abilities.name: Explosiveness
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in your hand when you are setting up to play, you may put it face down as your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Seeking Fang
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.flavorText: Luxray can see through solid objects. It will instantly spot prey trying to hide behind walls, even if the walls are thick.

cards.name: Rotom V

abilities.name: Instant Charge
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Scrap Short
attacks.text: Put any number of Pokémon Tool cards from your discard pile in the Lost Zone. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you put in the Lost Zone in this way.

cards.name: Rotom VSTAR
rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

VSTAR Power

attacks.name: Scrap Pulse
attacks.text: Put any number of Pokémon Tool cards from your discard pile in the Lost Zone. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you put in the Lost Zone in this way.

cards.name: Emolga

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.flavorText: As it flies, it scatters electricity around, so bird Pokémon keep their distance. That's why Emolga can keep all its food to itself.

cards.name: Eelektrik

abilities.name: Ad Hoc Shock
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.flavorText: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

cards.name: Helioptile
cards.flavorText: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon's electric moves.

cards.name: Heliolisk

attacks.name: Wild Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

cards.flavorText: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

cards.name: Radiant Charjabug

abilities.name: Shocking Block
abilities.text: Whenever any player attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokémon V, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon.

rules: Radiant Pokémon rule: You can't have more than 1 Radiant Pokémon in your deck.

attacks.name: Linear Attack
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

cards.name: Zeraora

attacks.name: Wild Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

cards.flavorText: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.

cards.name: Zeraora V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Thunderous Bolt
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

cards.name: Zeraora VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Reactive Pulse
attacks.text: This attack does 60 damage for each of your opponent's Pokémon in play that has an Ability.

attacks.name: Max Fist
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.name: Zeraora VSTAR
rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

VSTAR Power
LightningLightningLightningColorless → Lightning Storm Star

attacks.name: Crushing Beat
attacks.text: You may discard a Stadium in play.

cards.name: Pincurchin

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Continuous Tumble
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

cards.flavorText: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

cards.name: Exeggcute

attacks.name: Psy Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.flavorText: Though it may look like it's just a bunch of eggs, it's a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

cards.name: Exeggutor

attacks.name: Powerful Storm
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Each of Exeggutor's three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don't seem to be very interested in one another.

cards.name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Psypump
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Psychic Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Limit Break
attacks.text: If your opponent has 3 or fewer Prize cards remaining, this attack does 90 more damage.

cards.flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

cards.name: Mew V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Energy Mix
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Fusion Strike Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Psychic Leap
attacks.text: You may shuffle this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck.

cards.name: Girafarig

attacks.name: Double Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.flavorText: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.

cards.name: Lunatone

attacks.name: Cycle Draw
attacks.text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Moon Kinesis
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It's active on the night of a full moon.

cards.name: Dusclops

attacks.name: Fade to Black
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.flavorText: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.

cards.name: Tapu Lele

attacks.name: Energy Burst
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.

cards.name: Hatterene V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Horoscope
attacks.text: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck. You may attach any number of Energy cards you find there to this Pokémon. Put the other cards back in any order.

attacks.name: Teleportation Burst
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.name: Hatterene VMAX

abilities.name: Witch's Domain
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may move up to 2 damage counters from your Pokémon to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: G-Max Smite
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.name: Enamorus

attacks.name: Draining Kiss
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Loving Sympathy
attacks.text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 70 more damage.

cards.flavorText: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winterncomes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon's lovengives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

cards.name: Graveler
cards.flavorText: It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.

cards.name: Solrock

abilities.name: Sun Energy
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Lunatone.

cards.flavorText: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

cards.name: Baltoy
cards.flavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

cards.name: Riolu
cards.flavorText: It's exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.

cards.name: Pancham
cards.flavorText: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master's actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.

cards.name: Rockruff

attacks.name: Invite Out
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.

cards.name: Lycanroc

attacks.name: Midnight Fang
attacks.text: This attack does 80 less damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: This form of Lycanroc is reckless. It chargesnheadlong at its opponents, attacking without anyncare about what injuries it might receive.

cards.name: Koffing

attacks.name: Smog
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.flavorText: It adores polluted air. Some claim that Koffing used to be more plentiful in the Galar region than they are now.

cards.name: Absol

attacks.name: Lost Claw
attacks.text: Put a random card from your opponent's hand in the Lost Zone.

cards.flavorText: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

cards.name: Purrloin

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

cards.flavorText: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.

cards.name: Liepard

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

cards.flavorText: Don't be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

cards.name: Krokorok

attacks.name: Dredge Up
attacks.text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

cards.flavorText: It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful.

cards.name: Pangoro

attacks.name: Wild Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon is quick to anger, and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.

cards.name: Skrelp
cards.flavorText: It drifts in the ocean, blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokémon come to feast on the seaweed, Skrelp feasts on them instead.

cards.name: Dragalge

attacks.name: Rocket Poison
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. If this Pokémon evolved from Skrelp during this turn, put 8 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1 during Pokémon Checkup.

cards.flavorText: Dragalge uses a poisonous liquid capable of corroding metal to send tankers that enter its territory to the bottom of the sea.

cards.name: Hoopa

attacks.name: Assault Gate
attacks.text: If this Pokémon didn't move from the Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does nothing. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

cards.flavorText: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

cards.name: Galarian Meowth

attacks.name: Fasten Claws
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

cards.flavorText: Living with a savage, seafaring people hasntoughened this Pokémon's body so much thatnparts of it have turned to iron.

cards.name: Galarian Perrserker

attacks.name: Sharp Claws
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

cards.flavorText: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

cards.name: Scizor

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Dangerous Claws
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, this attack does 80 more damage.

cards.flavorText: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor's body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.

cards.name: Aron

attacks.name: Slight Intrusion
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

cards.flavorText: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

cards.name: Lairon

attacks.name: Wreak Havoc
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

cards.flavorText: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokémon often came into conflict with humans in the past.

cards.name: Aggron

attacks.name: Counter Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon equal to the damage done to this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.

cards.name: Metang

attacks.name: Bullet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

cards.flavorText: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.

cards.name: Pawniard

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

cards.flavorText: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.

cards.name: Pawniard
cards.flavorText: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.

cards.name: Bisharp

attacks.name: Spike Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

cards.flavorText: It's accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.

cards.name: Zacian

attacks.name: Battle Legion
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancientntimes, this Pokémon needs only a single strikento fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.

cards.name: Zacian V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Piercing Strike
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Behemoth Blade
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon VMAX, this attack does 160 more damage.

rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
